[
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-10T08:36:13+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467af",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-21T23:01:59+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae18544648f",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae18544648f",
    "text": "Opening files, post-mortems, prep. Black plays Sicilian. White plays Ruy Lopez or d4.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-10T08:36:13+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b0",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-21T23:01:59+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae18544648f",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae18544648f",
    "text": "Rules of the road",
    "type": "heading_2"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-10T08:36:13+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b1",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-21T23:01:59+00:00",
    "order": "2",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae18544648f",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae18544648f",
    "text": "Every loss gets a post-mortem before next session. No exceptions.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-18T16:31:05+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b2",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T18:36:05+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f3",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f3",
    "text": "Najdorf: 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6. Point of a6 is to deny b5 to White's pieces and prep ...e5 or ...e6.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-18T16:31:05+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b3",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T18:36:05+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f3",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f3",
    "text": "Main tries for White",
    "type": "heading_2"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-18T16:31:05+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b4",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T18:36:05+00:00",
    "order": "2",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f3",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f3",
    "text": "After 6.Bg5 e6 7.f4 Be7 is the classical main line. 6.Be3 English Attack is sharper, opposite-side castling.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-18T16:31:05+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b5",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-18T18:36:05+00:00",
    "order": "3",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f3",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f3",
    "text": "Drill the poisoned pawn line 7...Qb6 ten games on Lichess",
    "type": "to_do"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-23T00:53:53+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b6",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-19T15:14:37+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f4",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f4",
    "text": "English Attack: 6.Be3 e5 7.Nb3 Be6 8.f3 Be7 9.Qd2 O-O 10.O-O-O. Both sides race on opposite wings.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-23T00:53:53+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b7",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-19T15:14:37+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f4",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f4",
    "text": "Black gets ...Nbd7, ...b5, ...Nb6 with queenside play. Tempo counts. Do not waste a move.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-08-23T00:53:53+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b8",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-19T15:14:37+00:00",
    "order": "2",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f4",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f4",
    "text": "Memorize the ...b5-b4 vs Nd5 trade and when to take",
    "type": "to_do"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-09-01T11:00:46+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467b9",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-17T23:43:50+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f5",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f5",
    "text": "Nimzo: 1.d4 Nf6 2.c4 e6 3.Nc3 Bb4. Pin the knight, fight for e4. Rubinstein is 4.e3.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-09-01T11:00:46+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467ba",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-17T23:43:50+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f5",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f5",
    "text": "Plan as Black: trade on c3, double White's pawns, blockade the c4 square, then play against the structure.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-09-07T23:31:19+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467bb",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-11T17:14:54+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f6",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f6",
    "text": "Winawer: 1.e4 e6 2.d4 d5 3.Nc3 Bb4 4.e5 c5 5.a3 Bxc3+ 6.bxc3. White has the bishop pair, Black hits the center.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-09-07T23:31:19+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467bc",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-11T17:14:54+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f6",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f6",
    "text": "Bad bishop on c8 is the eternal French problem. Solve it or suffer. ...Qa5 hits c3 and ties White down.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-09-07T23:31:19+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467bd",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-11T17:14:54+00:00",
    "order": "2",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f6",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f6",
    "text": "Check the 7.Qg4 piece sac line and whether ...Ne7 holds",
    "type": "to_do"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-09-12T14:25:54+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467be",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-19T18:03:05+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f7",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f7",
    "text": "Caro Advance: 1.e4 c6 2.d4 d5 3.e5 Bf5. Get the light bishop out before ...e6 locks it in. That is the whole point.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-09-12T14:25:54+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467bf",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-19T18:03:05+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f7",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f7",
    "text": "Watch 4.Nf3 e6 5.Be2 with ideas of Nh4 hitting the bishop. Retreat ...Bg6, never ...Bg4 here.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-09-21T22:04:04+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c0",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-20T22:54:12+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f8",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f8",
    "text": "Berlin: 1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.Bb5 Nf6 4.O-O Nxe4 5.d4 Nd6 6.Bxc6 dxc6 7.dxe5 Nf5 8.Qxd8+ Kxd8. The endgame.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-09-21T22:04:04+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c1",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-20T22:54:12+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f8",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464f8",
    "text": "As White I avoid the Berlin wall. Play 4.d3 instead, keep queens on, slower buildup with c3 and Nbd2.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-10-02T08:12:44+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c2",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-22T09:40:00+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464fa",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464fa",
    "text": "KIA: Nf3, g3, Bg2, O-O, d3, Nbd2, e4. Same setup against almost anything. Knight to f1 then e3 or g3, then attack the king.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-10-02T08:12:44+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c3",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-22T09:40:00+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464fa",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464fa",
    "text": "Play the e5 pawn lever timing against the French structure five times",
    "type": "to_do"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-10-28T20:31:18+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c4",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-12T11:47:03+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464fe",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464fe",
    "text": "Fried Liver: 1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.Bc4 Nf6 4.Ng5 d5 5.exd5 Nxd5 6.Nxf7. Fell for it once. Never play 5...Nxd5, play 5...Na5.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-10-28T20:31:18+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c5",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-12T11:47:03+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464fe",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464fe",
    "text": "5...Na5 6.Bb5+ c6 7.dxc6 bxc6 8.Be2 h6 and the knight retreats. Black is fine, just play accurately.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-11-03T18:09:41+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c6",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-25T22:18:29+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464ff",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464ff",
    "text": "Lost to Roman Wednesday. Najdorf, English Attack. Got my move order wrong, played ...O-O before ...b5 and got mated.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-11-03T18:09:41+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c7",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-25T22:18:29+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464ff",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464ff",
    "text": "g4-g5 came too fast. Should have delayed castling and met the pawn storm with ...h5. Fix the move order.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-11-03T18:09:41+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c8",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-25T22:18:29+00:00",
    "order": "2",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464ff",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854464ff",
    "text": "Rematch Roman, same line, with the corrected order",
    "type": "to_do"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-11-09T09:14:52+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467c9",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-15T08:55:14+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446500",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446500",
    "text": "Had R+3 vs R+2 same side, threw away the win. Did not cut the king on the third rank. Lucena needs the bridge.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-11-09T09:14:52+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467ca",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-15T08:55:14+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446500",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446500",
    "text": "Rook belongs behind the passed pawn. Always. Drilled it wrong for years. Dvoretsky chapter four.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-12-05T10:51:44+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467cb",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-13T13:19:57+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446504",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446504",
    "text": "Lucena position: build the bridge. King to f7, pawn to e7, rook to the fourth rank to block the checks, then promote.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-12-05T10:51:44+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467cc",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-02-13T13:19:57+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446504",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446504",
    "text": "Philidor for the defense: keep the rook on the third rank until the pawn advances, then check from behind.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-12-11T19:38:02+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467cd",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-28T20:02:39+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446505",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446505",
    "text": "King and pawn: who has the opposition decides it. Count the squares. Key squares in front of the pawn win.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-12-11T19:38:02+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467ce",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-01-28T20:02:39+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446505",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446505",
    "text": "Solve twenty opposition and triangulation studies on the board, not the screen",
    "type": "to_do"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-12-27T14:11:33+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467cf",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-08T09:52:14+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446507",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446507",
    "text": "Nimzowitsch: prophylaxis is asking what the opponent wants, then stopping it before you do anything else.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-12-27T14:11:33+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467d0",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-08T09:52:14+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446507",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446507",
    "text": "Overprotect the strong point. Blockade the passed pawn with a knight. These two ideas show up every game.",
    "type": "bulleted_list_item"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-11-22T12:03:55+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467d1",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-05T14:08:41+00:00",
    "order": "0",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446502",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446502",
    "text": "Round 1 prep. Likely 1.e4. If Open Sicilian, go Najdorf. If anti-Sicilian Alapin, ...d5 equalizes clean.",
    "type": "paragraph"
  },
  {
    "checked": "false",
    "created_time": "2025-11-22T12:03:55+00:00",
    "has_children": "false",
    "id": "bea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae1854467d2",
    "last_edited_time": "2026-03-05T14:08:41+00:00",
    "order": "1",
    "page_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446502",
    "parent_block_id": "pea790e4a248dab6ac4b6ae185446502",
